The Kaduna State Police Command has confirmed the raid on another rehabilitation centre in Kaduna, where 147 inmates mostly in shackles were found. According to the Kaduna police, Gov. Nasir  El-Rufa’i led the operation at the centre which had male and female inmates. <img class="size-full wp-image-1236508 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=640%2C389&#038;ssl=1" alt="El-Rufai" width="640" height="389" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=300%2C182&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=768%2C466&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=1024%2C622&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=58%2C35&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=260%2C158&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=200%2C121&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=560%2C340&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Command Public Relations Officer, DSP Yakubu Sabo confirmed the raid in a press statement issued on Saturday in Kaduna. He said that the police raided NIGAS Rehabilitation and Skills Acquisition Centre located at Rigasa in Igabi Local Government Area, at about 8 am on Saturday Sabo explained that during the raid, some of the inmates made certain allegations of maltreatment including sexual molestation particularly by the female inmates against some male inmates. “Following this discovery, the governor directed that all the inmates were evacuated to Hajj Camp located at Mando Kaduna for proper profiling and safe custody. “Similarly, the Police have arrested one Dr Lawal Muduru, also known as Malam Niga, the owner of the Centre to investigate him on the said allegations. “He is currently helping with the investigation at the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department of the Command. “The Command is also investigating the authenticity and validity of the registration document the suspect claimed to possess,” he said. Sabo said the Commissioner of Police  Ali Janga had reiterated his commitment to fighting all forms of crime and criminality in the state without fear or favour. He appealed to the general public to continue to support the Command in the current battle against criminality. Vanguard Governor Nasir el-Rufai on Saturday led a team of policemen on an impromptu visit to Malam Niga's rehabilitation Centre at Rigasa Community in Igabi Local Government Area of Kaduna State where one hundred and forty-seven men, women and children were rescued and taken into protective custody by the Kaduna State… October 19, 2019 In "News" Governor Nasir el-Rufai on Saturday led a team of policemen on an impromptu visit to Malam Niga's rehabilitation Centre at Rigasa Community in Igabi Local Government Area of Kaduna State where one hundred and forty-seven men, women and children were rescued and taken into protective custody by the Kaduna State… October 19, 2019 In "News" The police have shut down a religious centre housing some “maltreated children” in the Sabon Garin area of Daura in Katsina state. October 14, 2019 In "News"